Here's <b>Elisabeth</b>,our latest Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Elisabeth lives at <a href="http://dev.millsberry.com/home/?user=dolphin0014"><a href='/home/?user=dolphin0014'>71121 Summer Street</a></a> in Golden Valley&mdash;a neighborhood she loves her for its scenic farms and fields&mdash;and has been a citizen since June 13, 2005.<br><br>We found Elisabeth energetically hopping around town, so it came as no surprise to hear that her physical fitness is super strong. Elisabeth's also very friendly, charming, and smart. Her interests include music, drawing, and mysteries. The latest mystery she's been trying to solve is who's been munching on her Cinnamon Toast Crunch plant! <br><br>When not tracking mystery munchers, Elisabeth likes to organize her 17 shimmering trophies, lining them up by size. Her most prized trophy is from the America's Second Harvest Food Drive. <br><br>In her spare time, Elisabeth likes to hang out at the movie theater, the mall, and sometimes, the Millsberry town pool. If you want to buy her a CD, her favorite music is country&mdash;and nothing else!<br><br>So say hello next time you see this model citizen around town, or give a big wave if you spot her in a cinnamon swirl jungle car!<br></div>
